  "text": "Information on nitrogen efficiency in triticale is even more limited than that for phosphorus. In a study with twelve triticale genotypes grown in soil in pots significant genetic variation was found in N efficiency calculated by the ratio of grain yield to N absorbed by the above-ground plant parts at maturity [CITATION_1] .",
